ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa talked tough at the party's last NEC meeting of the year and made the announcement that secretary-general Ace Magashule would be appearing before the Integrity Committee during his closing address on Tuesday.  Courtesy of #DStv403 PRETORIA - ANC Secretary-General Ace Magashule will present himself to the party's Integrity Commission on 12 December. ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa talked tough at the party's last NEC meeting of the year and made the announcement during his closing address on Tuesday. Ramaphosa insisted that the party's resolutions must be implemented. EXCLUSIVE: Magashule says he is not corrupt "We will fully implement the mandate of the 54th National Conference and the decisions made by the NEC, understanding that these are fundamental to the renewal of the organisation and to the restoration of the credibility of the movement among South Africans," Ramaphosa said. "We will be consistent and even-handed in the application of these decisions and will ensure that fair and due process is followed." Ramaphosa also said ANC members must use maximum discipline and refrain from "unbecoming" behaviour that denigrates the African National Congress.